snippet: Onavo, a start-up based in Tel Aviv, has been bought by Facebook as part of its Internet.org effort to bring free or low-cost Internet access to billions around the world without it.
abstract: Onavo, a start-up based in Tel Aviv, has been bought by Facebook as part of its Internet.org effort to bring free or low-cost Internet access to billions around the world without it.

headline.main: Facebook Buys Israeli Maker of Data Compression Software for Mobile Web Effort
headline.print_headline: Facebook Buys Israeli Maker of Data-Compression Software for Mobile Web Effort
